I wanted to like this place when I went in to buy a specialty soda. I wanted in line for 10 minutes while the cashier typed some stuff on the computer (???) and chatted and laughed with the only customer in front of me. The customer even had his ...MoreI wanted to like this place when I went in to buy a specialty soda. I wanted in line for 10 minutes while the cashier typed some stuff on the computer (???) and chatted and laughed with the only customer in front of me. The customer even had his money on the counter to pay, which just sat there the whole time I was in line. The cashier completely ignored me, not even a "I'll be right with you." Then she proceeded to escort the customer over to the cigar/cigarette counter and kept chatting and laughing with him. I put the soda back and just walked out. Horrible service and won't go back even though this place looked cool inside. So lame. The cashier should be fired. No other employees offered to help either.

This is a great place to grab brunch at on the weekends. Parking isn't terrible. Also, if you can seat outside, that would be ideal, but it gets crowded in the afternoons on the weekend. They have mimosas like most places for brunch. Their mac ...MoreThis is a great place to grab brunch at on the weekends. Parking isn't terrible. Also, if you can seat outside, that would be ideal, but it gets crowded in the afternoons on the weekend. They have mimosas like most places for brunch. Their mac & cheese with bacon and local hot sauce is amazing! I highly recommend it. I had the Fried Egg Sandwich with avocado, but it was missing something. It wasn't quite complete. However, another one of their sandwiches, which I can't find on the menu right now was pretty amazing. All in all, I recommend this place for brunch. And of course, I have to come for their oyster night on Mondays for half off oysters and write a review on that. :)

This review is regarding brunch. Although there's a small brunch menu there's surely something for everyone: yogurt parfait, bangers & eggs, smoked trout, biscuits & gravy. I went with the classic breakfast sandwich ($11 with bacon): poached eggs ...MoreThis review is regarding brunch. Although there's a small brunch menu there's surely something for everyone: yogurt parfait, bangers & eggs, smoked trout, biscuits & gravy. I went with the classic breakfast sandwich ($11 with bacon): poached eggs, ripe avocado, sprouts (I so miss sprouts on menus), fried green tomato and bacon (optional) on Texas toast. It was very tasty; my only disappointment was the fried green tomato (hard to discern it from a potato as it needed ripening). The bacon gets 10 stars in my book: thick, meaty and crispy. I'll be back just for the bacon alone. For dessert I had the "brulee grapefruit" ($4): a Texas grapefruit half topped with raw sugar and broiled. And they serve delicious Stumptown coffee.
